# Git Ignore File for ICU Sedation Digital Twin Research
#
# This file tells Git which files and directories should not be tracked
# in version control. Proper use of gitignore is essential for medical
# research repositories because we want to share our analysis code
# without accidentally sharing patient data or large files that should
# not be in the repository.
#
# The most important categories we exclude are patient data files which
# are protected by data use agreements, large intermediate computational
# results that can be regenerated from code, Python cache and bytecode
# files that should not be shared, virtual environment directories, and
# editor configuration that varies between users.

# Patient data files must NEVER be committed to the repository.
# These files are governed by the MIMIC-IV data use agreement which
# prohibits redistribution. Our gitignore excludes any CSV files in
# the data directory by default, with the assumption that all such
# files are derived from MIMIC-IV.
data/*.csv
data/*.csv.gz
data/raw/
data/mimic/
data/processed_features/*.pkl
*demographics*.csv
*propofol*.csv
*sas*.csv
*kidney*.csv
*demo_*.csv

# Cached feature files are large and can be regenerated by running
# the feature building script. They should not be committed.
cached_features.pkl
ablation_features*.pkl
*.pkl

# Python compilation artifacts and caches
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python

# Virtual environments should never be committed because they are
# specific to each user's system and can be very large
venv/
env/
.venv/
.env/
ENV/

# Build artifacts and packaging metadata
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
*.egg

# Jupyter notebook checkpoint files
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Editor and IDE specific configuration files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Operating system metadata files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

# Credentials and secrets must never be committed for security
*credentials*.json
*service-account*.json
.env.local
*.key
*.pem
gcloud-config.json

# Large output files that can be regenerated
*.h5
*.hdf5

# Coverage and testing artifacts
.coverage
.pytest_cache/
htmlcov/
.tox/

# Temporary working files
tmp/
temp/
scratch/
